The article discusses the importance of military spouses and their sacrifices in supporting the armed forces. It highlights the challenges that military spouses face, including frequent moves, deployments, and the added difficulties brought on by the COVID-19 pandemic. The article emphasizes the need to support military spouses and provides examples of initiatives aimed at empowering them, such as the First Lady's work with Joining Forces and the Military Spouse Employment Partnership. The article concludes by proclaiming May 7th as Military Spouse Appreciation Day and calling upon the American people to honor military spouses.